  "elapsed_s": 18.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was talking about Yossel Davidovics.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yossel Davidovics, we used to call him Yossel [NON-ENGLISH], because-- you asked me about nicknames.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is one that had a nickname.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The reason why was because [NON-ENGLISH], in Yiddish, means the heavyset one, because there was another Yossel that happened to be also with the same name, but he wasn't heavyset.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So you had to distinguish between the two.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we called him Yossel [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I said Yossel Davidovics.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, I remember he turned around to his son, that could have been, at that time, maybe 17, 18 years of age, and his name was Moishe Leib.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said to him, I told you to put my [NON-ENGLISH] bottle-- to put it in the backpack, whatever they had, and it wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He says, and you forgot, and he says, how does a Jew travel without a [NON-ENGLISH] and without a [NON-ENGLISH]?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If this is our last journey-- this might be our last journey.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember overhearing this here, and it hit me because I considered him a wise man, and that he sized up the situation.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This might be our last journey.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What it turned out, it was his last journey, and his son's, and his wife's, and his other children's.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There's two daughters survived the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anyway, we got to the city of Yasinya.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't remember how long it took.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It must it must have taken us four or five hours, and we got unloaded there and were loaded up in Yasinya.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
